tip.text: The amount of delicious sandwiches this place serves is impressive. Fillings are super generous and there is so much choice. Don't make the mistake of not trying them out!
Try the Onglet or Bavette with million dollar fries and some of the lovely butters. Great spot!
Fantastic location, service and food. The large chicken wings are massive but you can ask to take any leftovers home. Best to make a reservation. Stellar service.
Huge amount of cakes, great breakfast and brunch options as well. Salmon Crostini is delicious with a green juice.
Try the delicious tasting menu with wine pairing. Service was great. I will definitely be back!
Belgian / Asian restaurant that serves delicious curries in large portions. Try the red curry with duck which was outstanding. Good service.
Great concept - a bookstore and restaurant in one. Extensive menu with lots of delicious looking options. The Gargamel Toast/Sandwich was very good.

tip.text: Very cute little Italian café in Bray that was so lovely it's hard to describe. Wonderful sandwiches.
Awesome pub full of craft beers and board games. Try the 1 kg chicken wings - spicy and delicious! More than enough for two.
Take the chef's table - an absolutely delicious experience. Our waiter Joni made sure we had everything we needed. We will definitely come back.

formattedAddress: Moevenpick Hotel Bur Dubai (19th Street Oud Metha)

tip.text: Good for people watching. Only tried one tapas dish which was good, but the sangria was a let down.
Lovely key lime pie - supposedly the best in town. Getting a whole pie is cheaper when with a group of 5. Have a great shop with lots of key lime pie flavoured sauces, cookies, etc.

venue.name: Kermit's Key West Key Lime Shoppe

tip.text: Snapper's is a seaside restaurant with an extensive menu! We liked the conch fritters, gator bites and the lobster tail. Fast service as well. Worth a stop on your drive to and from Key West!
The filet mignon with blue cheese was delicious. Great service but a little pricey. Somehow all wine was 50% off when we were here! I recommend the El Enemigo Malbec. Will definitely be back.
Pretty good BBQ restaurant with lots of options and nice atmosphere. Chips were a little soggy.
Cozy and inexpensive place for dinner. The spare ribs are good. At night Het Pakhuis is a great place to come for a dance and a drink!
For an environmentally friendly way to visit the Everglades and see tons of gators, go for a bike ride in Shark Valley! Amazing!
Great spicy chicken wings, ribs and deep fried Oreos. Nice cocktails as well.
The nacho starter here is pretty amazing and huge! Enough for two. Sadly the service wasn't great and a mandatory 20% tip was added to our bill.
The Mojitos here were great but this place is incredibly loud. I can't believe people take their kids here.
Great outdoor space with food trucks and a nice bar area. They do happy hours. The pulled pork fries, Scottish egg and truffle parmesan fries were good. They also do lots of craft beers.
Very comfortable business hotel with a nice rooftop pool area. The breakfast buffet was good. Dubai Mall and the Burj Khalifa are within walking distance.
Lots of choice in this restaurant in Nation Galleria. Try the Coffee Lab options.  Delicious pizza as well.
Gorgeous suites overlooking the perfect Santorini view. Little private pools both in the rooms and on the patios. This place is really something special!
Resort style hotel with gorgeous sea views and a nice pool area. They prepare a package for you if you plan to go to the beach. Fantastic location at JBR the walk.
Nicely laid out pool with Burj Khalifa views, palm trees and a swim-up bar. They will bring you a little cooler with water when you get a sunbed. Service can be slow.
Don't miss Ravi while in Dubai - truly delicious Indian food. They will make recommendations when you ask. This place will definitely not break the bank either! Highly recommended.

formattedAddress: Karama - Opposite Burjuman & Centerpoint (Sheikh Khalifa Bin Zayed Road)

tip.text: An actual Irish village in Dubai! Come here for pints, live music, rugby matches, soda bread and great craic!
Excellent hotel with gorgeous pool area, very large rooms and well above average breakfast buffet. Breakfast is expensive at 145 AED pp though.

venue.name: Swim & Tonic @ Steigenberger Business Hotel, Business Bay, Dubai

tip.text: Wow! Xico offers tasty Mexican food and cocktails and they do 50% off on food and drinks on Mondays! Try the jalapeño business!
The list of delicious options in this kitschy tea/brunch/lunch place is endless! Come here if you want something different!
Gorgeous Deluxe Studio with a gorgeous pool area. Close to Jumbo Supermarket but away from crowded Palm Beach. We will be back!
What a wonderful bed and breakfast! The view here is stunning, the rooms very comfortable and the breakfast delicious. Super friendly owners. So many reasons to stay here when in the north!
Good Japanse restaurant in the Temple Bar area. Try the Rainbow Roll with a Kirin!

contact.facebookName: Eatokyo Asian Fine Noodles and Sushi Bar

tip.text: This place has a beautiful terrace overlooking the valley. The duck main course was cooked to perfection. Recommended!
Beer garden with a nice setting but mediocre service. Couldn't find a waiter for a long time.
Restaurant with outdoor seating above the market hall. Great value! The 19 euro 3 course lunch menu is more than enough to leave you in a food coma for the rest of the day.

tip.text: Lovely floating bar/restaurant on the river. Did not serve food or snacks before 19:30 on a friday but we had really nice drinks in the sun. Recommended.
Great selection of Korean dishes and beers and a nice cosy bar!
Great little restaurant - three courses for €35,-. Add a bottle of wine for €18,-.
Go up to the 45th floor and have a fancy cocktail overlooking the Tokyo nighttime skyline. A must when in Tokyo. Great service, great cocktails, a perfect view!
